00:13.346 --> 00:14.806
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, HEY) ♪

00:14.889 --> 00:16.933
♪ MIGHTY (LA, LA, LA) ♪

00:17.183 --> 00:19.477
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:19.728 --> 00:21.771
♪ I GOT THE BEAT SO ALL THE KIDS
DANCE WITH ME, ME, ME, ME ♪

00:22.105 --> 00:25.817
♪ STICK 'EM UP, ALL AROUND,
HERE COMES MIGHTY B, B, B, B ♪

00:26.067 --> 00:29.779
[♪...]

00:29.863 --> 00:31.740
♪ COME ON, EVERYBODY,
MIGHTY B ♪

00:32.073 --> 00:33.658
♪ MIGHTY, MIGHTY B. ♪

00:33.908 --> 00:35.702
[MUSIC ENDS]

00:37.203 --> 00:40.707
{\an8}Captioning Provided By:
MTV NETWORKS

00:40.957 --> 00:43.126
[♪...]

00:47.422 --> 00:48.339
HAPPY!

00:47.422 --> 00:48.339
{\an1}[BARKING]

00:48.673 --> 00:50.008
HEEL, HEEL.

00:50.258 --> 00:51.301
[CAT YOWLS]

00:50.258 --> 00:51.301
HEEL... UH!

00:51.634 --> 00:53.636
[CAT SCREAMS]

00:53.887 --> 00:55.889
Bessie: HEEL, HEEL, HAPPY.

00:56.181 --> 00:59.184
{\an5}[CAT SHRIEKS]

00:56.181 --> 00:59.184
[DOG PANTS]

00:59.517 --> 01:00.643
OOH.

00:59.517 --> 01:00.643
{\an1}[GRUNTS]

01:00.977 --> 01:02.187
[GASPS]

01:02.437 --> 01:03.772
Bessie: WHAT IS THIS PLACE?

01:04.063 --> 01:05.147
[GASPING HOWL]

01:05.397 --> 01:07.066
{\an3}[WHIMPERS]

01:07.317 --> 01:08.985
[LONG GASP...]

01:09.068 --> 01:11.446
WOW... CRUSHED VELVET.

01:11.696 --> 01:13.406
GLAMOROUS [GASPS].

01:13.656 --> 01:15.283
SIT DOWN, CHILD.

01:15.533 --> 01:17.577
{\an1}MADAME VALESKA HAS
BEEN WAITING FOR YOU.

01:17.827 --> 01:19.829
YOU HAVE?

01:19.913 --> 01:21.831
UH, DID I FORGET TO CANCEL
ANOTHER APPOINTMENT?

01:21.915 --> 01:24.709
{\an1}YOU CAN'T CANCEL AN
APPOINTMENT WITH DESTINY.

01:24.959 --> 01:26.169
DO YOU WANT TO KNOW
YOUR FUTURE, CHILD?

01:26.419 --> 01:28.338
FOR A SMALL FEE, OF COURSE.

01:28.588 --> 01:30.757
NO THANKS,
I ALREADY KNOW IT.

01:31.090 --> 01:33.301
{\an5}I'M GONNA TURN
INTO THE MIGHTY B,
A TOTALLY AWESOME SUPERHERO.

01:33.551 --> 01:35.929
{\an3}I JUST HAVE TO EARN EVERY SINGLE
BADGE IN THE HONEYBEE HANDBOOK

01:36.221 --> 01:38.848
{\an5}WHICH NO HONEYBEE HAS
EVER DONE BEFORE AND IT
ISN'T AS EASY AS IT SOUNDS

01:38.932 --> 01:41.851
AND THEN I WILL TRANSFORM
INTO THE MIGHTY B.

01:41.935 --> 01:43.144
VALIANTLY SAVING...

01:43.394 --> 01:45.021
WELL, I HAVE A 3:30

01:45.313 --> 01:47.732
{\an1}BUT IT LOOKS LIKE
SOMEONE HAS <i> THE GIFT.</i>

01:47.982 --> 01:50.026
HUH, WHAT GIFT?

01:50.109 --> 01:51.861
WELL, OBVIOUSLY YOU
CAN SEE THE FUTURE.

01:51.945 --> 01:54.572
WAIT, DO YOU MEAN...

01:54.823 --> 01:57.367
[SLOWLY]: E.S.P.?

01:57.617 --> 01:58.701
UH-YEAH, THAT'S RIGHT.

01:58.952 --> 02:00.537
I KNEW IT.

02:00.787 --> 02:02.831
SEE, NOW BE ON
YOUR WAY, MESSY

02:03.081 --> 02:05.041
AND SHARE YOUR GIFT
WITH THE WORLD.

02:05.124 --> 02:06.709
OK.

02:06.960 --> 02:08.586
[HORRIFIED GASP]

02:08.836 --> 02:09.086
[WHISPERS]: HOW DO
YOU KNOW MY NAME?

02:11.464 --> 02:12.298
AWESOME.

02:15.927 --> 02:18.221
[MUMBLING...]

02:18.471 --> 02:20.765
THERE <i> IS</i> AN E.S.P. BADGE,
I KNEW IT.

02:21.015 --> 02:22.517
[GASPS]

02:22.767 --> 02:23.518
I KNEW IT.

02:28.606 --> 02:29.732
WHAT'LL IT BE?

02:29.983 --> 02:31.609
I'LL HAVE...

02:31.860 --> 02:33.069
{\an3}WAIT-WAIT-WAIT-WAIT,
DON'T TELL ME.

02:33.152 --> 02:35.405
<i>EGGS...</i>

02:35.655 --> 02:37.240
{\an1}ALL RIGHT,
AND A SIDE OF...

02:37.490 --> 02:38.366
<i>TOAST...</i>

02:41.703 --> 02:44.664
{\an1}HERE'S AN INVITATION TO
MY BIRTHDAY PARTY, BESSIE.

02:44.914 --> 02:45.957
IT'S A BIG ONE.

02:46.249 --> 02:47.709
I'M HALFWAY TO A HUNDRED.

02:47.959 --> 02:49.669
SEE?

02:49.919 --> 02:51.838
SILENCE, I HAVE E.S.P.

02:52.171 --> 02:54.632
I'M SEEING THE FUTURE.

02:54.883 --> 02:56.968
[GASPS]: WOW.

02:57.260 --> 02:59.345
ARE THERE DINOSAURS THERE?

02:59.596 --> 03:01.431
YOU WANT THE STUFFED
FRENCH TOAST

03:01.681 --> 03:02.849
BUT YOU'RE GONNA GET
A PROTEIN SCRAMBLE.

03:03.099 --> 03:04.100
IS IT THAT OBVIOUS?

03:04.183 --> 03:05.810
{\an3}WHOA...

03:06.060 --> 03:08.396
{\an1}YOU'RE GONNA
LEAVE THE SEAT UP.

03:08.646 --> 03:10.523
{\an3}AS A COURTESY
TO THE NEXT GUY.

03:10.773 --> 03:12.567
{\an1}WOW.

03:12.817 --> 03:14.736
Bessie: YOU'RE GONNA
LEAVE A SMALL TIP.

03:14.986 --> 03:16.946
{\an1}IN EUROPE,
10 PERCENT IS STANDARD.

03:17.030 --> 03:19.532
WELL, 15 PERCENT IS NICE,
SO COUGH IT UP, MISTER.

03:23.036 --> 03:25.079
<i>VIVA LA FRANCE.</i>

03:25.163 --> 03:29.500
WOW, CAN YOU SEE ANYTHING
ABOUT MY BIRTHDAY PARTY?

03:29.751 --> 03:32.295
OH, IT'S TOO HARD.

03:32.545 --> 03:35.089
FOR THAT I'LL NEED
MY CRYSTAL BALL.

03:35.340 --> 03:36.674
{\an1}COME ON.

03:36.925 --> 03:38.009
[CRYSTAL BALL CLINKS]

03:38.092 --> 03:40.011
{\an3}BIRTHDAY...

03:40.261 --> 03:42.597
{\an3}<i>BIRTHDAY...</i>

03:42.847 --> 03:44.140
{\an3}[DRAMATICALLY]:
I SEE A VERY

03:44.223 --> 03:47.560
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.

03:47.810 --> 03:49.938
OH, AM I UNWRAPPING A PONY?

03:53.149 --> 03:53.983
{\an3}UH-HUH.

03:54.233 --> 03:54.943
IS THERE CANDY?

03:57.362 --> 03:59.989
{\an3}Bessie: TO...
TAL-LY... TOTALLY.

04:00.073 --> 04:02.158
TONS AND TONS OF CANDY.

04:02.241 --> 04:03.993
YOU'RE THE QUEEN
OF CANDY COUNTY

04:04.285 --> 04:06.037
AND IT'S YOUR BIRTHDAY

04:06.120 --> 04:07.872
{\an3}AND ALL YOUR
SUBJECTS ARE THERE.

04:08.122 --> 04:09.415
I HOPE MATT'S NOT THERE.

04:12.085 --> 04:14.671
Bessie: AND IT'S RAINING
CANDY CONFETTI.

04:19.175 --> 04:20.885
...AND THERE'S STREAMERS
MADE OUT OF LICORICE.

04:24.138 --> 04:26.432
THERE'S A RIVER MADE OUT OF
ROOT BEER IN THE BACK YARD.

04:26.683 --> 04:28.101
Penny: ALL FOR ME?

04:28.351 --> 04:29.894
[LOUD BURP]

04:30.144 --> 04:31.187
Bessie: BUT WAIT, THERE'S MORE.

04:31.479 --> 04:32.814
THERE'S A TAFFY SLIDE.

04:33.064 --> 04:35.400
Penny: WHEE...

04:35.650 --> 04:37.443
Bessie: AND I HOPE
YOU LIKE PRESENTS.

04:37.694 --> 04:40.279
Penny: I DO, I DO,
HOW'D YOU KNOW THAT?

04:40.530 --> 04:43.199
Bessie: BECAUSE YOU'RE
GETTING A MOUNTAIN OF THEM.

04:43.282 --> 04:45.368
[EXHAUSTED]: AH, OOH.

04:45.618 --> 04:47.120
I NEED TO REST.

04:47.412 --> 04:49.122
{\an3}OH, THAT TAKES
A LOT OUT OF ME.

04:49.414 --> 04:50.832
OK, THAT'S ALL I GOT.

04:51.082 --> 04:53.501
OH, BUT YOU REALLY SAW A PONY?

04:53.751 --> 04:56.212
PENNY, I'M THE <i> AMAZING</i> BESSIE.

04:56.295 --> 04:57.839
DON'T YOU TRUST MY VISION?

04:58.089 --> 04:59.507
OF COURSE, I DO.

04:59.757 --> 05:03.594
YEE... MY OWN PONY.

05:03.845 --> 05:05.513
I'M GONNA GO HOME AND
SET UP HIS LITTER BOX.

05:10.310 --> 05:12.228
[YAWNING]

05:12.311 --> 05:13.396
WAKE UP.

05:13.646 --> 05:14.647
[TWITTERING]

05:14.897 --> 05:16.024
[GASPS]

05:16.274 --> 05:17.483
[TWITTERING]

05:17.734 --> 05:18.317
[TWITTERING AND CHIRPING...]

05:22.905 --> 05:24.073
THANK YOU, MY LADIES.

05:24.323 --> 05:25.408
[TWITTERING]

05:25.658 --> 05:26.826
[LOUD SLAP]

05:27.076 --> 05:30.121
GOOD DAY, FATHER.

05:30.413 --> 05:33.082
UH, OH-OH, AH,
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, PRINCESS.

05:33.374 --> 05:35.168
QUEEN, YOU MEAN.

05:35.418 --> 05:37.712
I MUST AWAY TO THE HIVE
WHERE LADY BESSIE

05:37.962 --> 05:40.381
WILL ADORN ME
IN BIRTHDAY FINERY.

05:40.631 --> 05:43.968
YEAH, SOUNDS GOOD,
CHICKEN, HAVE FUN.

05:44.218 --> 05:47.638
I WILL RETURN THREE HOURS HENCE
FOR MY GLORIOUS CELEBRATION.

05:47.889 --> 05:51.017
{\an3}UM-HM, UH, DON'T
FORGET YOUR INHALER.

05:51.267 --> 05:53.811
Bessie: AND NOW
QUEEN OF CANDY COUNTY

05:54.062 --> 05:55.188
FOR THE
FINISHING TOUCH...

05:55.521 --> 05:58.816
[IMITATING TRUMPET FANFARE]

05:59.067 --> 06:00.318
HUZZAH!

06:02.904 --> 06:04.489
ONE LAST THING.

06:04.739 --> 06:09.160
{\an1}A BLINDFOLD FOR
MAXIMUM AWESOMENESS.

06:09.243 --> 06:12.121
OK, ONE, TWO...
ARE YOU READY?

06:12.371 --> 06:15.166
[INHALES] READY.

06:15.249 --> 06:18.169
[IMITATING FANFARE]:
♪ BUM-BUM, BUM ♪

06:18.252 --> 06:19.587
♪ BUM, BUM-BUM, BUM,
BUM-BUM, BUM ♪

06:19.837 --> 06:22.048
BEHOLD, A BIRTHDAY PARADISE.

06:22.298 --> 06:23.800
Penny: CAN I LOOK?

06:24.050 --> 06:25.051
IS IT EVERYTHING
YOU SAW, BESSIE?

06:25.384 --> 06:26.511
WELL... THERE'S CAKE.

06:29.138 --> 06:31.140
WHO'S LENNY?

06:31.224 --> 06:33.017
[FATHER CHUCKLES]

06:33.267 --> 06:37.313
MM, OOPSIE,
IT'S... CHOCOLATE.

06:37.396 --> 06:38.648
IT WAS HALF OFF AT WAKE'N'CAKE.

06:38.898 --> 06:40.483
UH, CLEARANCE CAKE?

06:40.733 --> 06:41.984
{\an3}I'LL PASS.

06:42.235 --> 06:43.236
UM... THAT'S NOT ALL.

06:43.528 --> 06:45.321
I'VE GOT SOMETHING ELSE

06:45.404 --> 06:46.739
IT STARTS WITH A "P"...

06:46.989 --> 06:48.199
IS IT MY PONY?

06:48.282 --> 06:50.118
IT'S A <i> PIÑATA.</i>

06:55.248 --> 06:57.416
I DON'T WANT A "TWIÑATA".

06:57.667 --> 06:59.252
WHERE'S MY PONY?

06:59.502 --> 07:01.212
{\an3}WHERE'S MY ROOT
BEER RIVER?

07:01.295 --> 07:02.588
WHERE'S MY
DUMP TRUCK?

07:02.839 --> 07:04.924
I... I DON'T KNOW, PENNY.

07:05.174 --> 07:06.926
I'M SORRY.

07:07.176 --> 07:10.596
I GUESS I DON'T
HAVE E.S.P. AFTER ALL.

07:10.847 --> 07:13.349
I REALLY THOUGHT
I SAW A CANDY COUNTY.

07:13.641 --> 07:15.184
WELL, GUESS WHAT I SEE?

07:15.268 --> 07:17.353
ME NOT TALKING TO YOU.

07:17.645 --> 07:19.522
AND NEITHER IS MY PONY!

07:19.605 --> 07:21.524
{\an3}[CRYING]

07:21.774 --> 07:23.442
[HYSTERICAL SOBBING]:
I... DON'T... WANNA...

07:23.693 --> 07:25.027
BUT CHICKEN,
I GOT ICE CREAM, TOO.

07:25.278 --> 07:27.113
RUM RAISIN.

07:27.363 --> 07:29.740
WELL... WELL, I WAS
RIGHT ABOUT THE CAKE.

07:29.991 --> 07:31.242
[BIKE BELL DINGS]

07:31.325 --> 07:33.202
GIVE ME A BREAK, FINGER.

07:33.286 --> 07:34.412
MADAME VALESKA SAID
I HAD THE GIFT.

07:36.330 --> 07:40.168
[SIGHS] THERE GOES
MY E.S.P. BADGE.

07:40.418 --> 07:42.211
YOU KNOW, IT'S EASY TO GIVE
ADVICE SOMETIMES, FINGER.

07:42.295 --> 07:45.339
JUST REMEMBER THAT,
IT'S EASY TO GIVE ADVICE.

07:45.423 --> 07:47.341
WELL, TAKE THAT
STUPID PARTY HAT OFF.

07:47.675 --> 07:50.720
I CAN'T TALK TO YOU, I, UH...

07:50.970 --> 07:53.306
{\an5}IT'S JUST HARD FOR ME
TO TAKE ADVICE SOMETIMES,
I'M SORRY, THAT'S THE WAY...

07:53.639 --> 07:56.100
WHAT AM I SUPPOSED TO DO?

07:56.350 --> 07:57.977
{\an5}TRY MY HARDEST AND THROW
THE PARTY THAT I THOUGHT
I SAW IN THE FUTURE?

07:58.227 --> 07:59.770
WHAT?

08:00.021 --> 08:01.272
[DISTANT HORN HONKS]

08:01.355 --> 08:03.774
OW, FINGER.

08:03.858 --> 08:04.984
[GASPS]

08:10.156 --> 08:11.407
MY MOUNTAIN.

08:11.490 --> 08:13.701
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

08:13.951 --> 08:15.703
{\an5}I DON'T HAVE TIME
TO EXPLAIN THE COMPLEX
CHAIN OF EVENTS

08:15.953 --> 08:18.206
THAT HAVE LED UP
TO THIS MOMENT, BEN

08:18.456 --> 08:20.333
BUT I HAVE TO THROW THE WORLD'S
MOST SPECTACULAR PARTY FOR PENNY

08:20.416 --> 08:22.543
{\an1}TO MAKE UP FOR THE FACT
THAT I THOUGHT I HAD E.S.P.

08:22.793 --> 08:24.837
{\an4}SO I PREDICTED THAT
SHE WAS GONNA HAVE
A "CANDYRIFIC" BIRTHDAY.

08:25.087 --> 08:27.256
BUT I MUST HAVE LOST MY POWER
SOMEHOW 'CAUSE IT TURNED OUT

08:27.548 --> 08:29.592
{\an4}THAT ALL SHE GOT WAS
SOMEONE ELSE'S BAR MITZVAH
SHEET CAKE AND A "TWIÑATA."

08:29.842 --> 08:31.719
{\an4}SO NOW DESPITE
THE CRASHING BLOW
MY EGO HAS TAKEN

08:31.969 --> 08:33.511
AS A RESULT OF LOSING MY
ABILITY TO SEE THE FUTURE

08:33.763 --> 08:35.972
{\an1}I HAVE TO PUT MY
PERSONAL PAIN ASIDE

08:36.224 --> 08:38.351
{\an4}AND DO SOMETHING
TOTALLY AWESOME FOR HER
LIKE PLANNING A PARTY.

08:38.643 --> 08:39.894
SO ARE YOU
HELPING ME OR NOT?

08:40.144 --> 08:42.230
YES?

08:42.520 --> 08:44.273
GREAT, I'M SO GLAD
YOU'RE ON BOARD.

08:44.357 --> 08:45.316
GIVE ME YOUR
HALLOWEEN CANDY.

08:57.745 --> 09:02.166
FAREWELL, SWEET RIBBON CANDY.

09:02.416 --> 09:05.253
[IMITATES WARNING ALERT]:
BOOP, BOOP, BOOP...

09:05.503 --> 09:06.379
BOOP, BACK IT UP.

09:06.629 --> 09:08.589
{\an3}BOOP, BOOP.

09:14.262 --> 09:15.137
[GURGLES]

09:14.262 --> 09:15.137
HUH?

09:15.471 --> 09:17.473
[SCREAMS]

09:17.723 --> 09:18.933
[SLURPING]

09:29.902 --> 09:31.445
[GULLS CRY]

09:33.781 --> 09:36.158
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

09:36.409 --> 09:37.326
{\an6}PENNY, QUEEN OF
CANDY COUNTY.

09:36.409 --> 09:37.326
[GASPS]

09:37.743 --> 09:39.203
YOUR HONORABLE SERVANT

09:39.453 --> 09:41.080
BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM

09:41.330 --> 09:42.373
REQUESTS YOUR
PRESENCE AT A PARTY

09:42.665 --> 09:45.751
THROWN IN YOUR HONOR.

09:46.002 --> 09:47.128
THAT MEANS IT'S FOR YOU.

09:47.378 --> 09:48.462
[SURPRISED GASP]

09:48.754 --> 09:50.631
A FOUR-LEGGED PONY.

09:50.881 --> 09:51.549
FOR ME?

09:53.551 --> 09:55.344
TO CANDY COUNTY, ANON.

09:55.636 --> 09:57.513
EMPLOY THY EXTRA LEGS.

09:57.596 --> 09:59.765
{\an3}[MOANS]

10:00.016 --> 10:02.143
[HAPPY GROANING...]

10:08.774 --> 10:10.234
All: SURPRISE!

10:14.488 --> 10:18.367
{\an1}[STERNLY]: BESSIE, I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE TRYING TO DO...

10:18.659 --> 10:20.286
[JOYFUL]: AND I LOVE IT!

10:20.536 --> 10:21.203
WELL, THAT'S NOT ALL.

10:23.581 --> 10:24.707
OW [CHUCKLES].

10:24.957 --> 10:26.876
OW, CANDY CONFETTI, OW.

10:27.126 --> 10:28.210
HAPPY BIRTHDAY, PENNY.

10:28.461 --> 10:29.670
LET'S RAGE!

10:29.920 --> 10:31.922
[LOUD MUSIC PLAYS]

10:32.006 --> 10:33.007
UHH...

10:33.257 --> 10:34.550
WHOA...

10:34.633 --> 10:35.426
[BOWLING PINS CRASH]

10:37.678 --> 10:40.723
[CHEERING AND WHOOPING]

10:40.973 --> 10:44.352
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

10:44.602 --> 10:45.394
YEAH.

10:44.602 --> 10:45.394
WHOO.

10:58.491 --> 11:00.117
[DISTANT HORN HONKS]

11:01.577 --> 11:03.245
UH, OOH, AH.

11:03.496 --> 11:04.914
[MOANING]: UHH...

11:05.164 --> 11:06.874
HI, BESSIE.

11:06.957 --> 11:08.959
{\an6}OH, WHAT
TIME IS IT?

11:06.957 --> 11:08.959
{\an1}MORNING.

11:09.293 --> 11:12.046
THAT WAS SOME PARTY.

11:12.296 --> 11:14.423
UH, YEAH, I'LL SAY.

11:14.507 --> 11:15.674
I BROUGHT YOU SOMETHING.

11:15.925 --> 11:18.594
IT'S AN E.S.P. BADGE.

11:18.886 --> 11:20.596
{\an1}BECAUSE YOU'RE AN
EXTRA SPECIAL PERSON.

11:20.679 --> 11:23.307
AWESOME...
OH, TOO SOON.

11:23.557 --> 11:25.184
{\an3}LISTEN, PENNY,
THANK YOU FOR THIS.

11:25.434 --> 11:26.519
I'LL CALL YOU LATER, OK?

11:26.769 --> 11:29.063
OK.

11:29.313 --> 11:29.355
COME ON, I THINK THERE'S STILL
SOME SHEET CAKE AT MY HOUSE.

11:34.527 --> 11:37.863
[TELEPHONE RINGING...]

11:38.114 --> 11:40.533
[TYPEWRITER KEYS CLACK]

11:44.078 --> 11:46.914
[DISTANT HORN HONKS]

11:47.164 --> 11:49.250
[BESSIE SIGHS]

11:49.500 --> 11:50.501
{\an1}FINALLY, SOME
QUALITY TIME TOGETHER.

11:50.751 --> 11:53.379
ISN'T THIS FUN?

11:53.629 --> 11:55.172
{\an5}NOTHING LIKE TINY BEADS
AND FISHING LINE TO KEEP
OUR BEE BONDS STRONG.

11:55.423 --> 11:57.049
[WHISPERING]

11:57.299 --> 11:59.093
OOH, WHAT YA WHISPERING ABOUT?

11:59.343 --> 11:59.718
[WHISPERING] HM?

12:03.514 --> 12:04.974
AH-HEM?

12:05.224 --> 12:06.642
AREN'T YOU GONNA
PASS IT ON?

12:06.892 --> 12:08.436
DOUBT IT...
AND IT'S GOOD.

12:08.727 --> 12:10.187
WELL, BEES ALWAYS
SHARE THEIR BUZZ.

12:10.438 --> 12:12.398
YOUR SECRET'S SAFE WITH ME.

12:12.648 --> 12:13.566
I'M REALLY GOOD
AT KEEPING SECRETS, GO AHEAD.

12:16.360 --> 12:19.864
[SLOW MOTION]: WAIT... NO...

12:20.114 --> 12:23.033
...DON'T ZIP IT UP.

12:23.284 --> 12:24.118
[THUD]

12:26.495 --> 12:29.081
IF PORTIA WON'T TELL
A FELLOW BEE HER SECRET

12:29.331 --> 12:31.876
IT'S GOTTA BE BIG.

12:32.126 --> 12:33.461
MAYBE SHE'S GOT
A SHARK IN HER BATHTUB.

12:33.794 --> 12:35.671
MAYBE SHE'S GOING BALD.

12:35.754 --> 12:36.881
MAYBE SHE GOT
ACCEPTED TO COLLEGE.

12:37.131 --> 12:38.424
[HAPPY GROANS]

12:38.674 --> 12:40.426
SHE CAN FOLD HER TONGUE.

12:40.676 --> 12:41.677
SHE DISCOVERED
A NEW PRIMATE SPECIES.

12:41.969 --> 12:43.929
SHE EATS CARDBOARD.

12:44.180 --> 12:45.389
SHE WON THE PRIZE
FROM THE BACK OF A CEREAL BOX.

12:45.639 --> 12:46.807
SHE LIKES DOG FOOD.

12:47.057 --> 12:48.684
HER REAL NAME IS PAPER TOWEL.

12:48.767 --> 12:50.686
MAYBE SHE'S
AFRAID OF PAPRIKA.

12:50.769 --> 12:53.063
{\an1}[GASPS] THAT'S IT,
SHE'S AFRAID OF PAPRIKA.

12:54.774 --> 12:56.484
SHE DOESN'T FLOSS?

12:56.817 --> 12:58.235
SHE HAS A MOLE ON HER BACK.

12:58.486 --> 13:00.488
SHE'S ALLERGIC TO VELCRO.

13:00.738 --> 13:02.406
SHE DOESN'T RECYCLE.

13:02.656 --> 13:04.742
[BACKGROUND CHATTER]

13:16.670 --> 13:19.173
OH, HOW DOES ANYBODY
FIND OUT ANYTHING, HAPPY?

13:19.423 --> 13:22.009
WHERE DO PEOPLE
GET THEIR INFORMATION?

13:22.259 --> 13:24.011
[GASPS]

13:24.261 --> 13:27.556
Bessie: "REPORTER
UNCOVERS SECRET PLOT."

13:27.640 --> 13:30.392
AHH...

13:30.643 --> 13:32.937
[KNOCKING]

13:33.187 --> 13:34.939
{\an5}BESSIE HIGGENBOTTOM, "HIVE
HERALD", CAN I TALK TO YOU
FOR A SECOND?

13:35.189 --> 13:36.565
MESSY, YOU KNOW I CAN'T
BE SEEN WITH YOU.

13:36.649 --> 13:38.651
I GOT A REP TO PROTECT.

13:38.984 --> 13:41.362
UM-HM, UM-HM, I JUST NEED YOU
TO ANSWER A FEW QUESTIONS

13:41.612 --> 13:43.489
ABOUT YOUR FRIEND,
PORTIA AND THIS...

13:43.739 --> 13:45.282
SECRET OF HERS.

13:45.533 --> 13:47.368
LOOK, I CAN'T DO THAT, A'IGHT?

13:47.618 --> 13:48.869
I PROMISED NOT TO TELL.

13:49.119 --> 13:50.871
CROSSED MY HEART AND EVERYTHING.

13:51.121 --> 13:52.164
AND I AIN'T TAKING
NO LOOK IN MY EYE.

13:52.414 --> 13:52.498
[BABY CRIES]

13:54.416 --> 13:55.709
[GIGGLING AND LAUGHING]

13:55.793 --> 13:57.378
EXCUSE ME, JANET BARLEY?

13:57.628 --> 13:59.380
{\an1}[SCREAMS]

13:57.628 --> 13:59.380
{\an3}AHH!

13:59.713 --> 14:01.590
YOU USED TO BABY-SIT
PORTIA GIBBONS, CORRECT?

14:01.674 --> 14:04.718
{\an1}UH, OH, YEAH, WHEN SHE
WAS IN MORNING KINDERGARTEN.

14:04.802 --> 14:06.595
INTERESTING.

14:06.679 --> 14:08.639
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT HER BIG SECRET?

14:08.722 --> 14:09.932
{\an1}LOOK, I DON'T KNOW WHAT
YOU'RE TALKING ABOUT.

14:10.182 --> 14:11.642
COME NOW, JANET...

14:11.725 --> 14:13.769
I THINK YOU DO.

14:16.855 --> 14:18.399
[BABY TALK]

14:18.649 --> 14:19.650
[PHONE RINGS]

14:19.733 --> 14:21.610
WHAT UP?

14:21.694 --> 14:23.112
HIGGENBOTTOM, HI, PERIL,
DON'T HANG UP.

14:23.362 --> 14:25.239
IF YOU COULD JUST TELL ME...

14:25.489 --> 14:26.448
BESSIE, YOU WANNA KNOW
SO BAD YOU CAN TASTE IT.

14:26.699 --> 14:27.950
YES.

14:28.200 --> 14:29.743
WELL, I GOT ONE THING TO SAY.

14:29.827 --> 14:31.620
NO COMMENT... LATER.

14:31.704 --> 14:33.789
[DIAL TONE]

14:33.872 --> 14:35.624
[PHONE RINGS]

14:35.874 --> 14:37.501
Gwen: I can see you
Sherlock Holmie.

14:37.751 --> 14:38.961
{\an3}[GASPS]

14:39.211 --> 14:40.671
[SIREN BLARES... HORN HONKS]

14:40.921 --> 14:42.673
WHAT CAN I GET
FOR YOU, SIR?

14:42.756 --> 14:44.800
{\an3}[DISGUISING VOICE]:
I'LL HAVE...

14:44.883 --> 14:46.051
{\an3}WHATEVER PORTIA GIBBONS
ORDERED ON SUNDAY.

14:46.302 --> 14:48.178
WHAT'D SHE GET?

14:48.429 --> 14:49.597
BESSIE, I NEVER REVEAL
WHAT MY CUSTOMERS ORDER.

14:49.930 --> 14:51.557
IT'S A HIGHLY PERSONAL MATTER.

14:51.890 --> 14:53.434
BUT MR. WU,
YOU CAN TELL ME ANYTHING.

14:53.684 --> 14:54.810
I'M A REPORTER.

14:54.893 --> 14:57.479
[NOISY CLAMOR]

14:57.730 --> 14:59.523
{\an1}UH, I THINK SHE
HAD HOT AND SOUR SOUP.

14:59.773 --> 15:01.692
{\an1}BUT IT WAS A BUFFET,
I CAN'T BE SURE.

15:01.775 --> 15:03.444
I WON'T QUOTE YOU,
DON'T WORRY.

15:03.694 --> 15:04.737
THANKS, MR. WU.

15:05.029 --> 15:06.322
YOU'RE HOLDING OUT ON ME.

15:06.572 --> 15:07.698
YOU MUST KNOW SOMETHING.

15:08.032 --> 15:10.117
I FOUND OUT ABOUT THE SOUP.

15:10.367 --> 15:12.828
I JUST NEED YOU TO
FILL IN A FEW BLANKS.

15:12.911 --> 15:14.413
[GRUNTS/GURGLES]

15:12.911 --> 15:14.413
UH-HUH.

15:14.747 --> 15:16.415
[GURGLING]

15:16.665 --> 15:18.626
DO YOU SPELL THAT
WITH A "G" OR A...

15:18.876 --> 15:20.336
[PHONE RINGS]

15:20.586 --> 15:23.672
[TYPEWRITER CLACKING]

15:23.756 --> 15:26.091
[PHONE RINGING...]

15:26.342 --> 15:29.720
I'M TELLING YOU FINGER, YOU
CAN'T USE <i> WHOM</i> IN THIS CONTEXT.

15:29.803 --> 15:32.848
IT SHOULD READ, "PORTIA,
<i>WHO</i> HAS A SECRET."

15:32.931 --> 15:34.183
ANYWAY, IT DOESN'T MATTER
'CAUSE WE DON'T HAVE A STORY.

15:36.518 --> 15:38.604
{\an1}[GROWLING]

15:38.854 --> 15:41.106
{\an3}I KNOW, HAPPY,
BUT I GOT NOTHING.

15:41.357 --> 15:43.150
I TOLD YOU, PEOPLE ARE SCARED.

15:43.400 --> 15:44.485
THEY DON'T WANNA
GIVE ANYTHING UP.

15:44.735 --> 15:46.487
[GROWLING]

15:46.737 --> 15:48.614
OH, SO THAT'S WHAT
YOU CARE ABOUT NOW?

15:48.864 --> 15:51.033
ALL THIS IS
IS SELLING PAPERS TO YOU?

15:51.283 --> 15:52.451
WHAT ABOUT THE TRUTH?

15:52.701 --> 15:53.827
[PHONE RINGS]

15:54.161 --> 15:57.164
HIGGENBOTTOM, I'M LISTENING.

15:57.414 --> 16:00.125
[HEAVY BREATHING]

16:00.376 --> 16:01.710
HELLO... HELLO?

16:01.794 --> 16:02.795
Penny: I can help you.

16:03.087 --> 16:05.089
WHO IS THIS?

16:05.339 --> 16:07.883
I can't tell you my name,
just call me... not Penny.

16:08.133 --> 16:11.053
NOT PENNY... OK.

16:11.303 --> 16:13.889
DO YOU KNOW WHAT PORTIA'S
SECRET IS, NOT PENNY?

16:13.972 --> 16:16.183
Not so fast, hack.

16:16.433 --> 16:17.643
Meet me by the merry-go-round
tomorrow at 10:00 a.m. sharp.

16:17.976 --> 16:20.896
Bring taffy... lots of taffy.

16:21.188 --> 16:22.523
And don't ever
call me here again.

16:22.773 --> 16:23.816
YOU CALLED ME.

16:24.149 --> 16:25.442
Now you're catching on.

16:25.693 --> 16:27.152
[CLICK... DIAL TONE]

16:27.403 --> 16:28.445
[CROWS CAWING]

16:27.403 --> 16:28.445
[BESSIE HUMS]

16:28.779 --> 16:30.739
[HUMMING...]

16:31.031 --> 16:31.156
DID YOU BRING THE TAFFY?

16:36.495 --> 16:37.830
FRESH.

16:38.122 --> 16:40.040
OOH, THAT'S GOOD.

16:40.290 --> 16:41.875
OK, NOW, PENNY, I HELD UP
MY END OF THE BARGAIN.

16:41.959 --> 16:43.377
NOW YOU HOLD UP YOURS.

16:43.627 --> 16:44.712
START TALKING.

16:44.962 --> 16:46.588
[SLURPING]

16:46.839 --> 16:47.840
WAIT, WHAT ARE
WE MEETING ABOUT?

16:48.090 --> 16:49.341
PORTIA- SECRET.

16:49.591 --> 16:50.884
OH-YEAH, OH-YEAH.

16:50.968 --> 16:53.387
ALL I CAN SAY IS...

16:53.637 --> 16:57.266
{\an3}PORTIA ISN'T REALLY FEELING
LIKE HERSELF THESE DAYS.

16:57.516 --> 17:00.185
ISN'T FEELING LIKE HERSELF.

17:00.436 --> 17:02.020
WHERE'D SHE...

17:02.271 --> 17:02.354
NEXT TIME BRING
MORE TAFFY.

17:04.647 --> 17:06.608
WHO WAS THAT?

17:10.695 --> 17:12.823
NOT FEELING LIKE
HERSELF... HMM.

17:13.115 --> 17:14.199
WHAT DOES IT MEAN?

17:14.450 --> 17:14.992
{\an3}IS IT CODE?

17:22.833 --> 17:25.961
FINGER, I'VE GOT IT.

17:26.044 --> 17:27.713
AND IT'S BIGGER THAN BOTH OF US.

17:28.047 --> 17:31.467
PORTIA IS... AN ALIEN.

17:31.717 --> 17:34.928
[LAUGHS]: THAT'S WHY
SHE NEVER GETS MY JOKES.

17:35.012 --> 17:36.764
AND THAT UGLY SCARF.

17:37.055 --> 17:39.558
SHE'S REACHED GESTATION
AND SHE'S MOLTING.

17:39.808 --> 17:42.352
IT ALSO EXPLAINS HER LOVE
FOR SQUISHY STICKERS.

17:42.603 --> 17:45.522
EVERYONE KNOWS THOSE
COME FROM SPACE GOO.

17:45.773 --> 17:46.648
HOW COULD WE NOT HAVE SEEN THIS?

17:48.942 --> 17:50.986
Bessie: WELL, FINGER...

17:51.069 --> 17:52.821
WHO WOULD'VE THOUGHT
A COUPLE ROOKIES LIKE US

17:52.905 --> 17:54.823
WERE SITTIN' ON
THE STORY OF A CENTURY.

17:54.907 --> 17:56.158
PORTIA [CHUCKLES].

17:56.408 --> 17:58.202
AN EXTRATERRESTRIAL.

17:58.452 --> 17:59.578
I SMELL A BOOK DEAL.

17:59.828 --> 18:01.872
[ANGRY BARKING]

18:01.955 --> 18:03.665
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
WE CAN'T GO TO PRESS WITH IT?

18:03.916 --> 18:05.209
SHE POINTED AT THE PLANET.

18:05.459 --> 18:06.502
SHE <i> HAS</i> SQUISHY STICKERS.

18:06.752 --> 18:08.420
[GRUFF BARK]

18:08.670 --> 18:10.714
NO, HAPPY,
I CAN'T NAME MY SOURCE.

18:10.964 --> 18:13.967
AND FRANKLY, I CAN'T
<i>BELIEVE</i> YOU WOULD ASK.

18:14.051 --> 18:15.469
[GROWLING BARK]

18:15.719 --> 18:18.013
FINE, I'LL GET YOU THIS PROOF

18:18.263 --> 18:20.641
YOU SEEM TO THINK
IS SO IMPORTANT.

18:24.770 --> 18:25.979
SORRY, YOUR OFFICE.

18:26.063 --> 18:27.731
[♪...]

18:37.991 --> 18:39.952
HMM... YUMMY.

19:01.932 --> 19:03.016
[HAPPY GROANING]

19:03.308 --> 19:05.435
THANKS, HAPPY.

19:05.686 --> 19:06.311
{\an3}THAT MEANS A LOT COMING FROM
A "POOCH-LITZER" PRIZE WINNER.

19:09.439 --> 19:12.067
WELL, THAT'S IT.

19:12.150 --> 19:14.027
TOMORROW THE SHOCKING
TRUTH WILL BE OUT.

19:14.319 --> 19:16.989
I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO FEEL, FINGER.

19:17.281 --> 19:20.784
I GUESS I FEEL BAD TELLING
EVERYONE PORTIA'S SECRET.

19:21.034 --> 19:22.744
I KNOW, I KNOW, FINGER.

19:22.995 --> 19:24.663
WHEN I BECAME A REPORTER
THREE DAYS AGO

19:24.913 --> 19:26.498
I SWORE AN OATH
TO TELL THE TRUTH.

19:26.748 --> 19:28.792
BUT I FEEL BAD-
SHE'S MY FRIEND.

19:29.042 --> 19:31.503
BUT SHE'S AN ALIEN,
AND THE WORLD NEEDS TO KNOW.

19:31.753 --> 19:33.422
BUT WHAT WILL HAPPEN
BACK ON HER HOME PLANET?

19:33.672 --> 19:35.382
WILL SHE HAVE TO REPEAT A GRADE?

19:35.632 --> 19:37.467
THAT'S NOT MY PROBLEM,
THIS IS BUSINESS.

19:37.718 --> 19:39.803
BUT I'M ONE OF HER FRIENDS.

19:40.053 --> 19:41.889
NO, YOU'RE A MEMBER OF THE
PRESS, DO WHAT'S RIGHT.

19:42.139 --> 19:43.974
DO WHAT'S NICE.

19:44.057 --> 19:46.977
UGH... THIS IS AN ETHICAL
DILEMMA AS OLD AS E-MAIL.

19:47.060 --> 19:47.603
[DOORBELL CHIMES]

19:51.148 --> 19:54.484
UM, PORTIA CAN'T TALK
TO YOU RIGHT NOW, BESSIE.

19:54.735 --> 19:57.446
SHE'S NOT EXACTLY
NORMAL TODAY [CHUCKLES].

19:57.696 --> 19:59.615
I COMMEND YOU, BRAVE SOUL

19:59.865 --> 20:01.575
ON RAISING PORTIA
AS YOUR OWN HUMAN OFFSPRING.

20:01.825 --> 20:03.160
I'M SURE HER SPECIES
IS GRATEFUL.

20:07.164 --> 20:08.999
[GASPS] SHE'S IN
HER LIQUID STATE.

20:12.169 --> 20:13.921
BLORK, BLEE-BLORK, BLEE...

20:14.212 --> 20:16.256
{\an1}BLAK-BLAK, RUN,
RUN FREE, PORTIA.

20:16.506 --> 20:18.467
GO HOME WHILE
YOU STILL CAN.

20:18.717 --> 20:20.761
BEFORE I REVEAL TO THE WORLD
THAT YOU ARE AN ALIEN.

20:21.011 --> 20:22.888
[GASP]

20:23.138 --> 20:24.056
WHY WOULD YOU THINK
PORTIA'S AN ALIEN, YO?

20:24.306 --> 20:25.933
THAT'S MESSED UP.

20:26.183 --> 20:27.935
{\an1}THE FACTS
DON'T LIE, LADIES.

20:28.268 --> 20:30.062
THIS STRANGE BEAST ONLY EATS
FOOD THAT'S BEEN LIQUEFIED.

20:30.395 --> 20:32.731
{\an1}SHE HAS TO WEAR A SCARF
TO COVER HER ALIEN MARKINGS

20:32.981 --> 20:34.900
{\an4}AND I SAW HER DO
A NATIVE PLANET DANCE
IN HER LIVING ROOM.

20:35.150 --> 20:35.901
{\an1}SHE'S GOT A GREEN FACE,
FOR PETE'S SAKE.

20:37.945 --> 20:40.781
{\an1}THIS IS YOUR LAST CHANCE,
MY SCALY FRIEND.

20:41.031 --> 20:43.408
{\an1}TOMORROW YOUR SECRET
WILL BE BLOWN WIDE OPEN.

20:43.659 --> 20:45.702
{\an1}I BETTER TRANSLATE INTO
ALIEN SO SHE UNDERSTANDS.

20:45.953 --> 20:47.746
BLEEK-BLORK-BLORK,
LEK-BLEEK.

20:47.996 --> 20:49.206
BESSIE, YOU WANNA
KNOW THE REAL-REAL?

20:52.501 --> 20:53.919
WHAT!

20:54.169 --> 20:55.671
HUH, PORTIA'S SECRET IS...

20:58.256 --> 20:59.591
SHE HAS LARYNGITIS.

20:59.841 --> 21:01.760
LARYNGITIS?

21:02.010 --> 21:03.136
{\an3}LARYNGITIS?

21:03.428 --> 21:04.513
RUN FOR YOUR LIVES!

21:06.974 --> 21:09.184
OH, WHAT A BUST.

21:09.267 --> 21:11.520
LET ME BREAK IT DOWN FOR YOU.

21:11.770 --> 21:14.106
THAT'S WHY SHE CAN ONLY EAT HER
FOOD ALL GOOPY AND DISGUSTING.

21:14.439 --> 21:17.442
HER MOM MAKES HER WEAR THAT UGLY
SCARF TO PROTECT HER THROAT.

21:17.693 --> 21:19.778
SHE CAN'T TALK.

21:20.028 --> 21:21.113
SHE WAS JUST TRYING TO
GET US TO CHANGE THE CHANNEL.

21:21.405 --> 21:23.115
AND THE FACE MASK IS SO

21:23.407 --> 21:25.993
SHE WON'T HAVE WRINKLES
AT AGE 12... DUH.

21:26.243 --> 21:28.453
{\an5}Bessie: WELL, HOW DO
YOU EXPLAIN THE WEIRD
DANCING ALL BY HERSELF?

21:28.704 --> 21:31.206
WHAT IS UP WITH THAT?

21:31.498 --> 21:33.959
{\an1}SOMETIMES WHEN I'M ALONE,
I TASTE MY BOOGERS.

21:34.209 --> 21:35.627
{\an3}[GAGGING]

21:35.877 --> 21:37.045
LARYNGITIS?

21:37.337 --> 21:39.464
OH, THAT'S THE SECRET?

21:39.715 --> 21:41.758
I THOUGHT I HAD CRACKED
THE BIGGEST STORY OF THE YEAR.

21:42.009 --> 21:44.094
I HAVE TO ADMIT,
I'M BITTERLY DISAPPOINTED.

21:44.386 --> 21:47.014
I'LL PROBABLY BE FIRED.

21:47.264 --> 21:50.559
{\an5}BUT, HEY, AT LEAST
PORTIA DOESN'T HAVE TO RUSH
HOME TO HER ALIEN PLANET.

21:50.809 --> 21:53.020
WE CAN ALL HANG OUT.

21:53.270 --> 21:54.312
{\an4}YOU GUYS, LET'S
PLAY SOMETHING THAT
PORTIA CAN BE APART OF.

21:54.563 --> 21:55.105
HOW 'BOUT CHARADES?

21:57.190 --> 21:59.234
WHAT'S THAT?

21:59.317 --> 22:01.194
I'LL TAKE YOUR SILENCE AS
A YES, ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

22:01.278 --> 22:02.988
{\an4}FIRST WORD,
CAT... CATAMARAN.

22:01.278 --> 22:02.988
UGH...

22:03.321 --> 22:04.865
{\an4}UH, CAT, CAT...
CAT STEVENS.

22:03.321 --> 22:04.865
[GRUNTING...]

22:05.198 --> 22:06.616
{\an1}NO, SOUNDS LIKE:
BLUE JEANS.

22:06.867 --> 22:09.077
{\an1}UM, BABA GANOUSH,
SHOE POLISH.

22:09.161 --> 22:11.079
{\an4}OK, HOT COFFEE,
OH, DON'T EAT... DON'T
DRINK THE HOT COFFEE.

22:11.163 --> 22:13.248
{\an1}BANDANAS, STAY WITH ME,
NO, I'M GOOD AT THIS.

22:13.331 --> 22:15.500
{\an5}BUTTERFLY, NO...
BUTTER AND FLIES.

22:13.331 --> 22:15.500
[CRYING]

22:15.834 --> 22:16.960
{\an5}FLYING... FLYING
STICK OF BUTTER.

22:15.834 --> 22:16.960
[GROANS]

22:17.294 --> 22:19.129
NO, HOT CROSS BUNS.

22:19.212 --> 22:20.797
{\an1}LAVA LAMP, LAVA...
<i>TWO</i> LAVA LAMPS.

22:21.048 --> 22:22.841
OPOSSUM, A SLEEPING PUPPY?

22:23.091 --> 22:24.134
IT'S A MOVIE,
IT'S A MOVIE, UM, UM...

22:24.426 --> 22:24.926
[BESSIE'S VOICE FADES...]

22:29.181 --> 22:31.808
[♪...]

23:09.096 --> 23:10.889
[CHILDREN GIGGLING]

23:11.139 --> 23:12.808
[CHILDREN LAUGHING]
